<i>of the striking Major Shlessinger,</i>

17
00:01:22,264 --> 00:01:24,279
一位布尔战争的英雄
<i>a hero of the Boer War,</i>

18
00:01:24,316 --> 00:01:26,324
不幸在Ladysmith保卫战斗中 成了瘸子
<i>sadly crippled in the defense of Ladysmith</i>

19
00:01:26,362 --> 00:01:29,558
现在投身于慈善事业
<i>and now engaged in charitable work.</i>

20
00:01:29,595 --> 00:01:31,111
Calder女士是他的护士
<i>His nurse is a Ms. Calder</i>

21
00:01:31,149 --> 00:01:35,876
值得注意的是 她不仅是他的信徒
<i>whose attentiveness suggests not only that she is his disciple but also</i>

22
00:01:35,913 --> 00:01:39,866
而且或许里面还有更为亲密的感情
<i>that tenderer feelings may be involved.</i>

23
00:01:40,618 --> 00:01:42,819
然而  最令人雀跃的是
<i>Most fascinating of all, however,</i>

24
00:01:42,856 --> 00:01:44,778
一位非常杰出的女士
<i>is an extraordinary woman,</i>

25
00:01:44,816 --> 00:01:48,491
能在任何群体中脱颖而出的人
<i>one who would stand out in any society,</i>

26
00:01:48,529 --> 00:01:51,712
Frances Carfax女士
<i>the Lady Frances Carfax.</i>

27
00:01:51,749 --> 00:01:55,034
我想有人会觉得她很前卫
<i>I suppose one would call her modern</i>

28
00:01:55,071 --> 00:01:56,673
除了她似乎是来自
<i>except that she seems to come from</i>

29
00:01:56,711 --> 00:01:59,550
某个古老的英国怪异贵族的分支
