<i>And those of us foolish enough to doubt her</i>

39
00:02:58,192 --> 00:03:02,319
很快就因出现在浅滩上的小船 而自食其言
<i>were soon rebuked by the sight of a skiff moored in the shallows</i>

40
00:03:02,357 --> 00:03:06,459
还有因为那位像我们招呼时 目光灼灼的船长
<i>and by the stern gaze of its captain when she greeted us within.</i>

41
00:03:12,386 --> 00:03:14,277
一次出人意料的精彩布道 牧师
A surprisingly jolly sermon, Vicar,

42
00:03:14,315 --> 00:03:16,244
非常之惊喜
a lot like a cat.

43
00:03:17,163 --> 00:03:20,988
她不仅不在乎给大家留下的印象
<i>Well, she appears to care not a jot what her fellow guests make of her</i>

44
00:03:21,027 --> 00:03:23,876
似乎也对自己给所到之处
<i>and seems quite insensible to the vivid impression</i>

45
00:03:23,912 --> 00:03:26,531
留下的活泼身影毫无察觉
<i>she creates wherever she goes.</i>

46
00:03:31,927 --> 00:03:33,707
我们都被逗乐了
<i>We were all amused certainly</i>

47
00:03:33,744 --> 00:03:36,195
看着她努力把小船驶离岸边
<i>at the sight of her trying to board the skiff,</i>

48
00:03:36,234 --> 00:03:39,811
但既然她有本事开船而来
<i>but since she had accomplished the outward journey with such skill,</i>

49
00:03:39,848 --> 00:03:41,165
我们没有理由认为
<i>we had no reason to suppose</i>

50
00:03:41,203 --> 00:03:45,889
她的返程会碰上更大的困难
<i>that her return voyage would present her with any greater difficulty</i>

51
00:03:45,926 --> 00:03:49,372
或者会预料到最后的结果
<i>or that it would end in the way that it did.</i>

52
00:04:15,094 --> 00:04:17,014
我决定翻越小山走回去
<i>I had decided to walk back across the fill</i>

53
00:04:17,052 --> 00:04:18,800
这样我就不必留在那些等待
<i>so I was not amongst those who waited</i>

54
00:04:18,838 --> 00:04:20,981
为Frances女士返航庆祝的人群中
<i>to cheer Lady Frances on her return.</i>

55
00:04:21,535 --> 00:04:23,981
我比预计的时间晚到了一点
<i>I arrived a little later at exactly the moment</i>

56
00:04:24,019 --> 00:04:26,984
当时的情况真是千钧一发
<i>when tragedy threatened to strike.</i>

57
00:04:27,489 --> 00:04:28,959
救命!
Help!

58
00:04:31,308 --> 00:04:33,279
