Help, here!

59
00:04:36,052 --> 00:04:39,639
救命!
Help!

60
00:04:40,743 --> 00:04:43,298
我当时无能为力 亲爱的福尔摩斯
<i>I was helpless, my dear Holmes,</i>

61
00:04:43,336 --> 00:04:44,775
无能为力
<i>helpless.</i>

62
00:04:45,568 --> 00:04:48,972
在我的一生中 我从未如此 感到自己的无力
<i>I have never felt so powerless in my life,</i>

63
00:04:49,009 --> 00:04:50,338
我本以为有人与我一样
<i>as powerless so I thought</i>

64
00:04:50,375 --> 00:04:52,372
那位坐在自己轮椅上的老兵
<i>as the old soldier in his wheelchair</i>

65
00:04:52,410 --> 00:04:56,589
也只能拼命呼救 来寻求帮助
<i>who had only been able to shout, it seemed, for help.</i>

66
00:04:56,626 --> 00:04:57,583
凭着阅历
<i>As with many men,</i>

67
00:04:57,622 --> 00:05:00,035
我早就注意到 一个某部分有残疾的人
<i>I have noticed a weakness in one part of the body</i>

68
00:05:00,072 --> 00:05:03,610
作为补偿 其它地方会有惊人的力量
<i>is compensated by great strength elsewhere.</i>

69
00:05:05,309 --> 00:05:06,717
尽管无法行走
<i>Unable to walk,</i>

70
00:05:06,755 --> 00:05:09,271
Shlessinger仍然能够奋力在水中游泳
<i>Shlessinger was yet able to swim powerfully</i>

71
00:05:09,308 --> 00:05:10,822
仅仅靠他的臂膀
<i>with his arms alone.</i>

72
00:05:18,190 --> 00:05:21,912
后来旅馆的援兵也及时赶到了
<i>Reinforcements arrived in due course from the hotel,</i>

73
00:05:21,949 --> 00:05:25,290
一场悲剧就这样被避免了
<i>and tragedy was happily averted.</i>

74
00:05:25,327 --> 00:05:27,250
现在 一切恢复正常
<i>Now, all parties are recovered,</i>

75
00:05:27,289 --> 00:05:29,613
据说Frances女士
<i>it is reported that the Lady Frances</i>

76
00:05:29,651 --> 00:05:31,373
不满自己的获救
<i>is resentful of her rescue</i>

77
00:05:31,410 --> 00:05:33,700
就好像是她的女权主张
<i>as if her suffragette principles</i>

78
00:05:33,737 --> 00:05:36,369
因此会成了一种让步
<i>had been somehow compromised.</i>

79
00:05:37,146 --> 00:05:38,172
但所有人都认同
<i>All agree at any rate</i>

80
00:05:38,210 --> 00:05:42,119
Shlessinger少校是当时的英雄
<i>that Major Shlessinger is the hero of the hour.</i>

81
00:05:42,677 --> 00:05:47,788
现在Calder女士的精力 都放到了霸道的爱慕上
<i>Ms. Calder's attentions are now translated into patent adoration.</i>

82
00:05:48,489 --> 00:05:50,711
毫无疑问 在明天旅馆里
<i>No doubt further praise will be in order</i>

83
00:05:50,749 --> 00:05:52,746
在他进行的传教士活动上
<i>when he lectures on his missionary activities</i>

84
00:05:52,785 --> 00:05:54,566
一定会听到更多的赞美之词
<i>at the hotel tomorrow.</i>

85
00:05:55,814 --> 00:06:01,291
顺便说一句 他是 基督医疗福音教会的英国代表
<i>He is, by the way, the British representative of the Mission Church of Christ the Healer</i>

86
00:06:01,328 --> 00:06:04,992
基地就在秘鲁的安第斯高地
<i>whose theater works in the high Andes of Peru.</i>

87
00:06:13,585 --> 00:06:14,943
早上好
Morning.

88
00:06:18,766 --> 00:06:21,868
Shlessinger少校在回避我
Major Shlessinger is avoiding me.

89
00:06:21,906 --> 00:06:25,831
可怜的人在为自己的 英勇行为感到尴尬
The poor man is embarrassed by his own heroism.

90
00:06:25,868 --> 00:06:29,197
也许他现在认为 我有义务为他的事业出一份力
Perhaps he now thinks I'm obliged to contribute to his work.

91
00:06:30,345 --> 00:06:33,306
人就是有这样显著的弱点
Men have such extraordinary weaknesses.

92
00:06:34,001 --> 00:06:34,900
你不这么想吗?
Don't you think.

93
00:06:34,938 --> 00:06:39,694
哦 是的 当然了 我们就是这样 当然 我赞同
Oh, yes, certainly, we do, of course, I agree.

94
00:06:40,774 --> 00:06:45,441
你介意到湖边转一转吗 医生
Would you care to take a turn by the lake, Doctor?

95
00:06:59,440 --> 00:07:02,332
Shlessinger少校为他的教会 不知疲倦的工作
Major Shlessinger works tirelessly for his church,

96
00:07:02,370 --> 00:07:03,641
不是吗
does he not?

97
00:07:03,679 --> 00:07:08,656
我明白他们需要大笔的资金
I understand the need for funds is considerable.

98
00:07:08,693 --> 00:07:11,027
明天他会在旅馆举办讲座
He's lecturing on his cause tomorrow

99
00:07:11,065 --> 00:07:12,483
希望能筹集到一些资金
here in the hotel hoping to raise some money.

100
00:07:12,521 --> 00:07:14,585
他会大有收获
He'll do well.

101
00:07:14,623 --> 00:07:17,072
当地妇女会很乐意各自 捐出半个几尼(英国旧金币)
The local matronage will happily part with half a guinea each

102
00:07:17,110 --> 00:07:21,411
得到一个和这样一位男士 在公共场所相处的机会
for the company of such a man all be it in public.

103
00:07:21,911 --> 00:07:23,225
我吓到你了吗
Do I shock you?

104
00:07:23,262 --> 00:07:24,565
一点也没有
Not at all.

105
00:07:24,603 --> 00:07:26,075
我吓到了我的哥哥
I shock my brother.

106
00:07:26,810 --> 00:07:27,579
作为Rufton伯爵
As the Earl of Rufton,

107
00:07:27,618 --> 00:07:30,968
我想他觉得有义务被吓到
I think he feels it is his duty to be shocked.

108
00:07:32,052 --> 00:07:34,960
啊 这里很漂亮 不是吗
Oh, it's very beautiful here, isn't it?

109
00:07:36,322 --> 00:07:39,896
我童年的每个夏天 都在这湖边度过
I spent every summer of my childhood here by this lake.

110
00:07:42,048 --> 00:07:43,681
美轮美奂
It's very beautiful.

111
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:45,126
确实如此
It is indeed.

112
00:07:48,063 --> 00:07:50,163
他明天会来看望我
He's to visit me tomorrow.

113
00:07:50,201 --> 00:07:51,306
谁?
Who?

114
00:07:51,344 --> 00:07:52,407
我的哥哥
My brother.

115
00:07:52,904 --> 00:07:55,231
这也是义务 当然了
That is duty, too, of course.

116
00:07:58,314 --> 00:07:59,621
该死的他
Damn him.

117
00:08:00,783 --> 00:08:02,908
该死的他!
Damn him.

118
00:08:23,146 --> 00:08:25,192
啊  Frances女士
Ah, Lady Frances.

119
00:08:26,979 --> 00:08:29,614
真是令人惊喜
What a pleasant surprise.

120
00:08:29,652 --> 00:08:31,792
我必须承认她的行为
<i>I must confess that her behavior</i>

121
00:08:31,830 --> 00:08:34,821
始终让我着迷
<i>continues to fascinate me.</i>

122
00:08:34,858 --> 00:08:36,936
我承认她对这个陌生的
<i>I grant that her reaction to this</i>

123
00:08:36,973 --> 00:08:39,572
骑马者的反应非常激烈
<i>unknown horseman was extreme,</i>

124
00:08:39,610 --> 00:08:42,481
但她的许多反应都是这样
<i>but many of her reactions are.</i>

125
00:08:42,519 --> 00:08:44,208
她是不是认识他呢 我在猜想
<i>Had she known him, I wonder?</i>

126
00:08:44,245 --> 00:08:48,664
过去发生了什么 让她对他如此害怕
<i>What lies in her past to prompt this fear of him?</i>

127
00:08:49,829 --> 00:08:51,333
为了寻找答案
<i>In looking for an explanation,</i>

128
00:08:51,370 --> 00:08:52,802
我期待着
<i>I am placing some hopes</i>

129
00:08:52,840 --> 00:08:54,231
今天下午 Rufton伯爵
<i>in the visit we expect this afternoon</i>

130
00:08:54,269 --> 00:08:56,819
她哥哥的到访
<i>from her brother, the Earl of Rufton.</i>

131
00:08:56,857 --> 00:09:00,958
据说 他的古怪与他妹妹
<i>By all accounts,his oddities are of an entirely different order</i>

132
00:09:00,995 --> 00:09:02,831
正好相反
<i>from those of his sister.</i>

133
00:09:02,868 --> 00:09:04,773
当她在嘲笑传统时
<i>Where she flouts convention,</i>

134
00:09:04,811 --> 00:09:07,287
他会把过去时代的习俗
<i>he has raised the conventions of a former era</i>

135
00:09:07,325 --> 00:09:09,606
上升到信仰的高度
<i>to the status of a faith.</i>

136
00:09:11,636 --> 00:09:12,653
而说到自己
<i>As for myself,</i>

137
00:09:12,691 --> 00:09:15,014
我注意到自己越来越漠视
<i>I notice an increasing indifference</i>

138
00:09:15,050 --> 00:09:17,278
周围的秀色美景
<i>to the natural beauty which lies about me.</i>

139
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:19,906
我的思绪时常回到
<i>My thoughts return constantly</i>

140
00:09:19,942 --> 00:09:21,756
Frances女士
<i>to the Lady Frances.</i>

141
00:09:22,374 --> 00:09:23,993
她的一些事情
<i>There is something about her life</i>

142
00:09:24,031 --> 00:09:25,011
会激起我的同情心
<i>which prompts my sympathy,</i>

143
00:09:25,049 --> 00:09:27,546
一些我可以感受到的悲伤
<i>some unhappiness I can sense</i>

144
00:09:27,584 --> 00:09:30,142
令我想把它们驱散
<i>which I would dearly like to dispel.</i>

145
00:09:31,429 --> 00:09:33,170
我寄希望她的精神
<i>It is to be hoped that her spirits</i>

146
00:09:33,207 --> 00:09:35,463
