167
00:10:46,007 --> 00:10:47,170
我们已经大不如前
The hall is falling to bits.

168
00:10:47,207 --> 00:10:49,707
在东翼有了猫头鹰的家族
There's a family of owls in the east wing,

169
00:10:49,745 --> 00:10:51,174
你自己想想吧
and you think.

170
00:10:51,212 --> 00:10:53,785
现在又是什么呢
What is it this time?

171
00:10:53,823 --> 00:10:57,215
帮助在Islington身无分文的诗人
Helping penniless poets in Islington?

172
00:10:57,252 --> 00:10:59,259
你只知道如何地残酷 是吧
You only know how to be cruel, don't you?

173
00:10:59,297 --> 00:11:01,905
你什么时候在乎过我要什么
When have you ever cared for what I want?

174
00:11:01,942 --> 00:11:05,132
我过去15年的岁月是如此可怜
The last 15 years of my life have been wretched

175
00:11:05,170 --> 00:11:07,996
而现在 至少 我有机会
and now, at last, I had a chance

176
00:11:08,033 --> 00:11:08,710
能做点什么事
to make something of it.

177
00:11:08,747 --> 00:11:11,037
这难道对你没有任何意义吗
Doesn't that have any meaning for you?

178
00:11:19,770 --> 00:11:21,522
下午好
Good Afternoon.

179
00:11:21,560 --> 00:11:24,380
我看不出任何区别
I don't see what difference it makes.

180
00:11:24,416 --> 00:11:25,074
区别就在于
The difference it makes

181
00:11:25,112 --> 00:11:26,910
我一直都在被你指挥
is that I'm being told what to do.

182
00:11:26,948 --> 00:11:28,126
你知道我讨厌这样
You know I loathe it.

183
00:11:28,165 --> 00:11:30,014
问题是你从来就不听取意见
The trouble is you won't even take advice,

184
00:11:30,051 --> 00:11:30,612
不是吗
will you?

185
00:11:30,650 --> 00:11:32,170
一切都给了你
You've been offered everything.

186
00:11:32,208 --> 00:11:33,199
却统统被你拒绝了
You've turned it all down.

187
00:11:33,236 --> 00:11:34,110
给了我什么?
What have I been offered?

188
00:11:34,148 --> 00:11:35,830
婚姻  美满的婚姻
Marriage, good marriages.

189
00:11:35,868 --> 00:11:37,426
哈 哈 哈...
Ha, ha, ha.

190
00:11:38,378 --> 00:11:42,037
给一个有头衔的乡下人做免费的奴隶
To be the unpaid slave of a titled yokel

191
00:11:42,074 --> 00:11:43,691
这种人连书都没看过一本
who hasn't even read a book,

192
00:11:43,729 --> 00:11:46,051
以为巴赫(音乐家)是种小猎犬
who thinks Bach is something terriers do.

193
00:11:46,089 --> 00:11:48,397
好吧 好吧
All right, all right.

194
00:11:48,434 --> 00:11:50,073
你还有什么反对我的理由?
What have you got against me doing this?

195
00:11:50,110 --> 00:11:51,915
有什么?
What?

196
00:11:51,954 --> 00:11:55,604
我要远离这种可悲混乱的生活
I want to get out of this miserable mess my life is in

197
00:11:55,641 --> 00:11:59,348
看在上帝的份上 让我做自己
to be my own woman, for God's sake,

198
00:11:59,385 --> 00:12:02,897
让我过一段充实的日子
to fulfill just a portion of my life.

199
00:12:02,936 --> 00:12:07,220
你为什么总是拖我的后腿
Why do you always hold me back?

200
00:12:08,698 --> 00:12:10,582
好好想想  John
Think of it, John,

201
00:12:10,618 --> 00:12:12,008
好好想想
think of it.

202
00:12:12,273 --> 00:12:13,626
只要一笔钱
Just one payment.

203
00:12:13,664 --> 00:12:14,895
就一次
One.

204
00:12:14,932 --> 00:12:17,055
你就可以永远摆脱我了
You could see the back of me forever.

205
00:12:17,092 --> 00:12:20,633
正如我们展示的骡子运输
The mule express as we have dubbed it

206
00:12:20,672 --> 00:12:23,195
每个月会递送邮件
brings the mail once a month.

207
00:12:23,232 --> 00:12:24,011
信件 当然了
Letters, of course,

208
00:12:24,049 --> 00:12:27,474
来自基督图书馆的精神粮食
and food for the mind from the Library of Christ.

209
00:12:27,511 --> 00:12:31,215
以及为我的人们带来健康的药品
And medicines for the well being of my flock

210
00:12:31,253 --> 00:12:38,560
就是这群你们看到的站在楼外 临时钟楼下的人们
whom you may see here posing outside the mission below a temporary belfry.

211
00:12:39,129 --> 00:12:41,026
在我向你们展示下一幅
When I show you the next picture

212
00:12:41,064 --> 00:12:43,964
我教会中一名领导成员的照片时
of a leading member of my congregation,

213
00:12:44,002 --> 00:12:47,856
你就会明白牧羊人和迷失的羔羊的寓言
you will understand how the parable of the shepherd and the lost sheep

214
00:12:47,893 --> 00:12:50,234
为什么在我们的传教中改成了
has become transmuted in our teaching

215
00:12:50,272 --> 00:12:53,674
牧人和迷失的美洲驼
into that of the llama herd and the lost llama.

216
00:12:55,176 --> 00:12:58,479
最后是我们的教堂
And finally, our church,

217
00:12:58,516 --> 00:13:02,884
虽然简陋 粗糙 破烂
humble as it is, rough and poor indeed,

218
00:13:02,922 --> 00:13:04,318
我可以骄傲地说
I'm proud to tell you

219
00:13:04,355 --> 00:13:05,117
上帝的言语
that the word of God

220
00:13:05,155 --> 00:13:08,538
在其中被激情地宣讲
is preached as fervently within its walls

221
00:13:08,576 --> 00:13:11,546
并收到了热烈欢快的响应
and is as joyously received there

222
00:13:11,583 --> 00:13:15,463
正如在本土的大教堂里一样
as in any great cathedral here at home.

223
00:13:18,289 --> 00:13:19,872
谢谢
Thank you.

224
00:13:24,521 --> 00:13:26,499
谢谢 谢谢
Thank you, thank you.

225
00:13:26,537 --> 00:13:29,418
正如我预料中的鼓舞人心
It was inspiring as I predicted.

226
00:13:29,455 --> 00:13:35,638
我很遗憾地说Shlessinger少校 行程紧凑 马不停蹄
I regret to say that the rigors of his itinerary press hard upon Major Shlessinger

227
00:13:35,676 --> 00:13:38,116
很快就要出发去Whitehaven
who will shortly be departing for Whitehaven.

228
00:13:38,154 --> 00:13:43,941
就让我们为了他可敬的传教团开始募捐吧
We shall be taking up a collection on behalf of his estimable mission, of course.

229
00:13:43,977 --> 00:13:45,016
你什么意思
What do you mean?

230
00:13:45,053 --> 00:13:47,638
我是说你能自己补救
I mean that the remedy lies in your own hands.

231
00:13:47,676 --> 00:13:48,322
怎么做?
How?

232
00:13:48,360 --> 00:13:50,069
你知道该怎么做
You know how.

233
00:13:50,108 --> 00:13:52,079
如果你是认真的 你会知道怎么做
If you're really serious, you'll know what to do,

234
00:13:52,116 --> 00:13:52,929
该死
damn it.

235
00:13:52,967 --> 00:13:54,256
我厌恶了你总是来求助于我
I'm sick of you coming to me

236
00:13:54,294 --> 00:13:55,725
就为了这些疯狂的念头
with these crackpot notions.

237
00:13:55,763 --> 00:13:57,920
你知道我的责任
You know my responsibilities.

238
00:13:57,957 --> 00:13:59,855
如果你没有放弃所有给你的机会
If you hadn't thrown away all your chances,

239
00:13:59,894 --> 00:14:01,394
也不会落到现在这个田地
you wouldn't be in this position now.

240
00:14:01,432 --> 00:14:03,231
我已经受够了
Well, I've had enough.

241
00:14:04,833 --> 00:14:06,334
你知道你该做什么
You know what you have to do.

242
00:14:06,371 --> 00:14:08,352
成熟点 去做吧
Grow up and do it.

243
00:14:08,389 --> 00:14:11,204
我最后的求助 这真的是我最后的求助
My last resort, my very last resort.

244
00:14:11,243 --> 00:14:13,060
你怎么能这么说
How can you suggest it.

245
00:14:13,331 --> 00:14:14,627
马夫
Groom.

246
00:14:15,538 --> 00:14:17,322
马夫
Groom.

247
00:14:17,632 --> 00:14:19,537
你到底在哪里
Where the devil are you?

248
00:15:05,171 --> 00:15:07,709
Shlessinger先生的见面会 是在哪个房间举行
In which room is Mr. Shlessinger's meeting taking place?

249
00:15:07,746 --> 00:15:11,588
我恐怕见面会已经在 半小时前结束了 女士
I am afraid the meeting finished half an hour ago, madam.

250
00:15:11,626 --> 00:15:13,998
Shlessinger先生即刻就要 动身去Whitehaven
Mr. Shlessinger will have left for Whitehaven by now.

251
00:15:14,035 --> 00:15:15,170
哦 是的
Oh, yes.

252
00:15:15,208 --> 00:15:17,299
是的 我忘记了
Yes, I've forgotten.

253
00:15:17,337 --> 00:15:18,741
谢谢
Thank you.

254
00:15:22,739 --> 00:15:24,639
Frances女士
Lady Frances.

255
00:15:33,619 --> 00:15:36,988
别来纠缠我!
Leave me alone.

256
00:15:40,362 --> 00:15:42,201
抱歉
Excuse me.

257
00:15:42,452 --> 00:15:44,219
你 先生
You, sir.

258
00:15:46,020 --> 00:15:46,806
无容置疑
<i>I've no doubt</i>

259
00:15:46,845 --> 00:15:49,533
你会告诉我这是无谓的担心 福尔摩斯
<i>you will tell me my fears are unfounded, Holmes,</i>

260
00:15:49,570 --> 00:15:51,809
但那个人的反复出现
<i>but the repeated appearance of this man</i>

261
00:15:51,847 --> 00:15:53,766
已经为她的生活蒙上了阴影
<i>has cast a shadow over her life</i>

262
00:15:53,804 --> 00:15:57,138
无论她多努力还是无法摆脱
<i>which try as she might she cannot lift.</i>

263
00:16:00,526 --> 00:16:04,667
"...Elmyria号上的悲剧 Rosenbloom家族继承人溺水身亡"
*PAPER*

264
00:16:09,583 --> 00:16:11,975
晚报 福尔摩斯先生
Evening paper, Mr. Holmes?

265
00:16:21,067 --> 00:16:24,478
Hudson太太 给我找辆出租车
Mrs. Hudson, fetch me a cab.

266
00:17:21,346 --> 00:17:22,763
Hudson太太
Mrs. Hudson.

267
00:17:22,800 --> 00:17:25,701
等电报局一开门
As soon as the telegraph office is opened,

268
00:17:27,233 --> 00:17:29,455
就给John 华生医生去份电报
to Dr. John Watson,

269
00:17:29,492 --> 00:17:32,674
湖滨旅馆  Felmire  Cumberland
Lake Hotel, Felmire, Cumberland.

270
00:17:32,711 --> 00:17:34,501
内容是什么  福尔摩斯先生
And what of Mr. Holmes?

271
00:17:34,538 --> 00:17:36,762
我就要走了 Hudson太太
I shall not be here, Mrs. Hudson.

272
00:17:36,800 --> 00:17:38,276
华生医生
Dr. Watson.

273
00:17:38,314 --> 00:17:41,062
我会在8:17离开Uston的车上
I shall be on the 8:17 out of Uston.

274
00:17:41,098 --> 00:17:42,521
华生医生
Dr. Watson.

275
00:17:42,559 --> 00:17:45,800
我的车在楼下等你
My cab awaits you downstairs.

276
00:17:46,703 --> 00:17:47,877
快读
Read.

277
00:17:47,915 --> 00:17:49,168
福尔摩斯先生
Mr. Holmes.

278
00:17:49,206 --> 00:17:50,328
快读
Read.

279
00:17:52,685 --> 00:17:56,032
巨大的危险 Frances女士 句号
Grave danger Lady Frances, stop.

280
00:17:56,071 --> 00:17:59,121
不要让她走出视线 句号
Never let from sight, stop.

281
00:17:59,158 --> 00:18:02,131
我在路上 福尔摩斯
On my way, Holmes.

282
00:18:02,169 --> 00:18:03,583
这份电报来了多久?
How long has this been here?

283
00:18:03,620 --> 00:18:05,050
我 嗯
I um.

284
00:18:39,993 --> 00:18:41,670
福尔摩斯
Holmes.

285
00:18:44,328 --> 00:18:45,963
失踪了 华生
Disappeared, Watson.

286
00:18:49,585 --> 00:18:50,594
失踪了
Disappeared.

287
00:18:50,632 --> 00:18:53,229
Frances女士结账了吗
Did Lady Frances pay her bill?

288
00:18:53,267 --> 00:18:54,373
没有先生
No, sir.

289
00:18:54,411 --> 00:18:57,185
她有叫任何交通工具吗
Did she order any transport?

290
00:18:57,222 --> 00:18:58,393
不 先生
No, sir.

291
00:18:58,431 --> 00:19:00,380
她有拿走自己的行李吗
And she took none of her luggage?

292
00:19:00,419 --> 00:19:02,867
我想没有 先生
We think not, sir.

293
00:19:03,961 --> 00:19:05,930
福尔摩斯先生在哪里
Where is Mr. Holmes?

294
00:19:09,342 --> 00:19:11,781
没有任何消息 福尔摩斯
Nothing yet, Holmes.

295
00:19:13,598 --> 00:19:15,555
我开始害怕最坏的结果
I'm beginning to fear the worst.

296
00:19:15,591 --> 00:19:16,482
要怪我自己
I blame myself.

297
00:19:16,520 --> 00:19:18,175
我知道我该抓住那个人
I knew I should have pursued that fellow.

298
00:19:18,213 --> 00:19:20,241
有一个可能性
It is a possibility.

299
00:19:21,350 --> 00:19:22,456
是什么
What is?

300
00:19:22,495 --> 00:19:24,562
你还没看出来吗 再明显不过了
Do you not see it? It is most conspicuous.

301
00:19:24,600 --> 00:19:25,682
什么
What?

302
00:19:25,720 --> 00:19:28,358
小船 华生 驶走的小船
The skiff, Watson, the sailing skiff.

303
00:19:28,396 --> 00:19:29,618
不在这里了
It's not here.

304
00:19:29,656 --> 00:19:30,429
非常正确
Precisely.

305
00:19:30,466 --> 00:19:33,850
很可能Frances Carfax女士在上面
It is possible there lies the Lady Frances Carfax

306
00:19:33,887 --> 00:19:35,242
悄悄地去了Avonside
silent road to Avonside.

307
00:19:35,280 --> 00:19:37,174
这是众所周知的最近的终点
It is the nearest railhead as you know.

308
00:19:37,212 --> 00:19:39,876
你是说这个人用船绑架走了她?
You don't mean that this fellow abducted her by boat?

309
00:19:39,913 --> 00:19:41,470
丝绸
Silk.

310
00:19:43,007 --> 00:19:45,520
这是三个最大可能性之一
It is one of the three more likely possibilities.

311
00:19:46,552 --> 00:19:50,615
最佳的法国缝纫  鸽灰色
Best French sewn, dove gray.

312
00:19:50,652 --> 00:19:51,940
她有一条灰色丝绸的披肩
She had a gray silk shawl.

313
00:19:51,978 --> 00:19:53,525
不 没有更有价值的线索了
No, well, that will tell us nothing more.

314
00:19:53,563 --> 00:19:55,765
是哪三个可能性  福尔摩斯
What are the three possibilities, Holmes?

315
00:19:55,802 --> 00:19:57,162
她通常在什么衣服时会戴上披肩?
In what did she usually wear the shawl?

316
00:19:57,200 --> 00:19:58,205
她外出时的衣服
Oh, her outside clothes.

317
00:19:58,243 --> 00:20:00,131
哪三个可能性?!
The three possibilities?

318
00:20:00,169 --> 00:20:02,658
她可能和预谋的绑匪一起走了
She may have run away with her intended abductor.

319
00:20:02,695 --> 00:20:04,752
或如你所说她被人用船绑架走了
He may have abducted her by boat as you suggest

320
00:20:04,790 --> 00:20:05,754
或是其他方法
or by some other means.

321
00:20:05,791 --> 00:20:08,455
也许她...考虑到她目前的情绪
She may, considering her emotional condition,

322
00:20:08,492 --> 00:20:10,408
被人乘虚而入受骗出走
have been deceived into going with him.

323
00:20:10,446 --> 00:20:11,223
这太难让人相信了
I can hardly believe that.

324
00:20:11,261 --> 00:20:12,983
她非常害怕他 相信我
She was terrified of him, believe me.

325
00:20:13,020 --> 00:20:14,423
我相信你
I believe you.

326
00:20:16,039 --> 00:20:18,436
是的
Yes.

327
00:20:18,474 --> 00:20:21,464
在狐狸的世界里迷路的小鸡
A stray chicken in the world of foxes.

328
00:20:21,501 --> 00:20:24,390
一旦她被抓了 就不会失踪了
Once she's gobbled up, she's hardly missed.

329
00:20:24,903 --> 00:20:26,212
来吧  华生
Come, Watson.

330
00:20:26,886 --> 00:20:28,601
我们的马应该备好了
And our horses should be saddled by now.

331
00:20:28,638 --> 00:20:29,204
马?
Horses?

332
00:20:29,242 --> 00:20:31,709
我选择骑马也许有些过分了
I have been somewhat extravagant in choice of mounts,

333
00:20:31,746 --> 00:20:34,327
但拖延会在这时产生危险
but delay must be dangerous in this matter.

334
00:20:34,365 --> 00:20:37,205
我们要在黄昏时到达Rufton伯爵府
We should be at Rufton Hall at dusk.

335
00:20:46,259 --> 00:20:48,848
我不知道什么让你这么有兴趣 先生
I don't see what possible interest it could have for you, sir.

336
00:20:48,990 --> 00:20:50,777
我向你保证 非常吸引我
Considerable interest I assure you.

337
00:20:50,919 --> 00:20:53,010
世界上最危险的事情之一
One of the most dangerous classes in the world

338
00:20:53,048 --> 00:20:55,459
就是单身的漂泊女子
is the drifting and friendless woman

339
00:20:55,496 --> 00:20:57,236
得不到保护和指引
with no one to protect and guide her.

340
00:20:57,273 --> 00:21:01,911
不可避免地会诱使别人犯罪
She is the inevitable inciter of crime in others.

341
00:21:01,948 --> 00:21:03,804
我对你妹妹失踪这件事
I treat the disappearance of your sister

342
00:21:03,842 --> 00:21:06,142
抱着非常严肃的态度
with utmost seriousness.

343
00:21:06,179 --> 00:21:07,994
你以为我不是吗
Do you think I do not?

344
00:21:08,032 --> 00:21:10,671
我不过是说你有点计较了
I'm merely suggesting that it is frivolous

345
00:21:10,709 --> 00:21:14,234
不肯告诉我你们到底在争吵什么
to keep from me the substance of your quarrel.

346
00:21:14,271 --> 00:21:15,827
就是在争吵之后
It was after all this quarrel

347
00:21:15,865 --> 00:21:18,442
她紧接着就失踪了
which immediately preceded her disappearance.

348
00:21:20,308 --> 00:21:21,350
也许这和她曾经认识的
Might it have something to do

349
00:21:21,388 --> 00:21:24,345
酗酒的诗人有关呢?
with a drunken poet she once knew?

350
00:21:24,978 --> 00:21:25,732
什么?
What?

351
00:21:25,770 --> 00:21:26,959
我从同事那获悉
I understand of my colleague

352
00:21:26,997 --> 00:21:29,661
她或许最近见过他
