539
00:33:10,011 --> 00:33:11,341
希望她会在这些年后
that she would look kindly on me

540
00:33:11,378 --> 00:33:13,009
她会好好对我
after all these years,

541
00:33:14,064 --> 00:33:16,378
但我可笑地因为她一直没结婚
but I was ridiculously encouraged by the fact

542
00:33:16,414 --> 00:33:18,616
这样的事实所鼓舞
that she was not married.

543
00:33:18,963 --> 00:33:21,065
而现在 我的愚蠢把她
And now, my stupidity has driven her

544
00:33:21,102 --> 00:33:24,108
推向了凶手的怀抱
into the arms of a murderer.

545
00:33:25,598 --> 00:33:27,272
我能做什么
What can I do?

546
00:33:28,824 --> 00:33:31,927
我什么都不能做吗?
Is there nothing I can do?

547
00:33:33,163 --> 00:33:35,613
Shlessinger看见过你吗
Does Shlessinger know you by sight?

548
00:33:35,615 --> 00:33:36,639
没有
No.

549
00:33:37,300 --> 00:33:40,464
啊  那么有件事你能做
Ah, well, then there is something that you can do.

550
00:33:40,501 --> 00:33:42,770
但这需要你的耐心
But it'll demand great patience.

551
00:33:42,807 --> 00:33:46,687
我已经等了15年了 福尔摩斯先生
I have waited for 15 years, Mr. Holmes.

552
00:33:46,724 --> 00:33:48,989
Shlessinger希望珠宝能卖个好价钱
Shlessinger's had a fair price for the jewelry

553
00:33:49,027 --> 00:33:50,226
而且不要被追问
and no questions asked.

554
00:33:50,263 --> 00:33:52,513
他肯定会再到Riley的店里
He'll almost certainly return to Riley's shop.

555
00:33:52,551 --> 00:33:54,640
还有Rosenbloom的遗物
And Rosenblooms attorney for the will.

556
00:33:54,678 --> 00:33:56,951
现在 把这张纸条给Riley
Now, give this note to Riley.

557
00:33:56,988 --> 00:33:58,899
他会让你在店里等候
He will let you wait at the shop.

558
00:33:58,937 --> 00:34:00,003
可能会等很长时间
It may be a long wait,

559
00:34:00,041 --> 00:34:03,116
但你必须要保持耐心
but you possess your soul in patience.

560
00:34:03,153 --> 00:34:05,950
最重要的是 不要使用暴力
And above all, no violence.

561
00:35:16,280 --> 00:35:17,601
延误了
It's late.

562
00:35:17,639 --> 00:35:19,862
应该早就到了
Well, it should have been here before now.

563
00:35:19,899 --> 00:35:23,977
他们说过这比普通的更花时间
Well, they say it took longer being out of the ordinary.

564
00:35:24,015 --> 00:35:26,521
亲爱的 提醒我一下地址
The address, dear, remind me.

565
00:35:28,990 --> 00:35:30,624
是的 先生 我能帮忙吗
Yes, sir, can I help?

566
00:35:30,662 --> 00:35:31,959
Argyle大街
Argyle Street.

567
00:35:31,997 --> 00:35:34,210
我在找Argyle大街
I'm looking for Argyle Street.

568
00:35:34,249 --> 00:35:36,231
在路口有个邮局
There's a post office round the corner.

569
00:35:36,267 --> 00:35:37,913
问问那里吧
Try there.

570
00:36:40,069 --> 00:36:43,054
Green先生 没有逮捕令 我们什么也不能做
Mr. Green, we can do nothing without a warrant.

571
00:36:43,091 --> 00:36:44,557
我忍不下去了
This is intolerable.

572
00:36:44,596 --> 00:36:46,686
在我们有了那个可怜的纸上签名之前
Until we have some wretched signature

573
00:36:46,723 --> 00:36:48,580
我们什么也不能做
on a piece of paper, we can do nothing.

574
00:36:48,617 --> 00:36:51,500
同时 这些恶棍可以随意摆布她
Meanwhile, these fiends can do with her what they will.

575
00:36:51,539 --> 00:36:53,697
你确定 你告诉了我所有的细节?
Are you certain that you've told me every detail?

576
00:36:53,697 --> 00:36:55,638
所有的细节 我发誓
Every detail, I promise.

577
00:36:55,676 --> 00:36:58,349
那把这字条送到苏格兰场
Then take this note to Scotland Yard.

578
00:36:58,387 --> 00:37:00,585
他们会明白其中的紧迫
They will understand the urgency of it.

579
00:37:00,623 --> 00:37:03,424
那我在那里等逮捕令
And I am to wait there for the warrant.

580
00:37:03,461 --> 00:37:05,179
你今天是不可能拿到的
You will not get it today.

581
00:37:06,659 --> 00:37:07,552
什么?
What?

582
00:37:07,590 --> 00:37:08,960
有些延迟是不可避免的
Some delay is inevitable.

583
00:37:08,998 --> 00:37:11,581
必须先找到当地法官
A magistrate must be found.

584
00:37:11,618 --> 00:37:15,367
法律程序我们只能推动它 不能驱赶它
The process of the law can be  encouraged but not goaded.

585
00:37:15,405 --> 00:37:18,822
看在上帝的份上 明天就太晚了
Tomorrow may be too late for God's sake.

586
00:37:18,859 --> 00:37:20,092
Green先生
Mr. Green,

587
00:37:20,130 --> 00:37:23,212
能做的一切我们都会做
everything that can be done will be done.

588
00:37:23,249 --> 00:37:24,647
去吧
Go.

589
00:37:27,788 --> 00:37:31,263
-明天就真的太晚了 -我很清楚
-Tomorrow may indeed be too late. -I'm well aware of it.

590
00:37:33,412 --> 00:37:35,399
带上武器  华生
Arm yourself, Watson.

591
00:37:36,219 --> 00:37:39,380
我们得一如既往地 不按常理出牌
We are as usual the irregulars

592
00:37:39,416 --> 00:37:41,022
必须去碰碰运气
who must take our luck together

593
00:37:41,222 --> 00:37:44,364
正如我们过去偶尔所为
as we have occasionally done in the past.

594
00:37:48,546 --> 00:37:50,591
明天早上八点
8:00 tomorrow morning,

595
00:37:50,630 --> 00:37:52,385
Brickston公墓
Brickston Cemetery.

596
00:38:17,274 --> 00:38:19,542
我想你被指错了路 先生
I fancy that you've been misdirected, sir.

597
00:38:19,580 --> 00:38:23,354
也许你该上街走到底试试
Possibly if you try further down the street.

598
00:38:23,391 --> 00:38:24,122
会的
That will do.

599
00:38:24,160 --> 00:38:25,298
我们没时间浪费了
We have no time to waste.

600
00:38:25,336 --> 00:38:26,608
你是Harry Peters
You are Harry Peters,

601
00:38:26,645 --> 00:38:29,402
之后是Albert Shlessinger少校
late Major Albert Shlessinger,

602
00:38:29,440 --> 00:38:30,611
布尔战争的老兵
veteran of the Boer War.

603
00:38:30,649 --> 00:38:31,921
更多的化名
Your further aliases

604
00:38:31,960 --> 00:38:33,833
我就不重复了 免得让你无聊
I will not bore you by repeating.

605
00:38:34,321 --> 00:38:36,526
你的名字是什么
And what is your name?

606
00:38:36,564 --> 00:38:37,996
夏洛克 福尔摩斯
Sherlock Holmes.

607
00:38:38,034 --> 00:38:40,758
我的朋友和同伴 我想你认识
My friend and companion I think you know.

608
00:38:40,794 --> 00:38:43,341
这所房子很快就会在警方的监视下
The house will shortly be under police observation

609
00:38:43,379 --> 00:38:45,101
直到逮捕令到达
until a warrant is prepared

610
00:38:45,138 --> 00:38:47,071
得到搜索的授权
authorizing a search of the premises.

611
00:38:47,109 --> 00:38:49,615
你的名字没有吓到我  福尔摩斯先生
Your name does not frighten me, Mr. Holmes.

612
00:38:49,653 --> 00:38:51,151
我没有什么可隐瞒的
I have nothing to hide.

613
00:38:51,151 --> 00:38:52,232
你有何贵干
What is your business?

614
00:38:52,270 --> 00:38:55,239
我在找Frances Carfax女士
I'm looking for the Lady Frances Carfax.

615
00:38:55,277 --> 00:38:57,024
很高兴听你这么说
I'm delighted to hear it.

616
00:38:57,061 --> 00:39:00,027
如果有人能找到她  我想那就是你
If anyone can find her, I imagine you can.

617
00:39:00,065 --> 00:39:02,699
也许到时候你能好心地来通知我一声
Perhaps you'd be so good as to tell me when you do.

618
00:39:02,736 --> 00:39:05,977
我有一张她将近100英镑的欠条
I've a note against her for nearly 100 pounds,

619
00:39:06,015 --> 00:39:07,411
但是还没有看到一个子儿
and nothing to show for it

620
00:39:07,449 --> 00:39:09,184
除了两件假首饰
but a couple of trumpery pendants

621
00:39:09,184 --> 00:39:11,168
买家连看都不想看
that the dealer would hardly look at.

622
00:39:11,509 --> 00:39:12,527
这女人在骗财
The woman's a leech.

623
00:39:12,564 --> 00:39:14,891
你怎么敢这么说 先生
How dare you, sir.

624
00:39:15,259 --> 00:39:18,186
你在我们面前装成了 一个在战场上受伤的瘸子
You imposed upon us as a man crippled in a military action.

625
00:39:18,224 --> 00:39:20,163
你才是骗子
You are a fraud.

626
00:39:21,125 --> 00:39:23,183
哦 或许在你对屠杀的定义下
Oh, it may not have been a military action

627
00:39:23,221 --> 00:39:26,704
那并不算是场军事行动 医生
to satisfy your standards of slaughter, Doctor,

628
00:39:26,741 --> 00:39:29,289
但对我而言已经是了
but it was enough for me.

629
00:39:30,493 --> 00:39:33,823
我佩服你的即兴创作
I salute your powers of improvisation, sir,

630
00:39:33,860 --> 00:39:36,574
和厚颜无耻 但这没有用
and your effrontery, but it will not do.

631
00:39:36,612 --> 00:39:38,126
哦 我没有在开玩笑
Oh, I'm perfectly serious.

632
00:39:38,164 --> 00:39:40,579
你找到她 我就欠你们一次
You find her, and I'm your debtor.

633
00:39:40,616 --> 00:39:43,475
我一定要搜查这里
I mean to go through this house until I do.

634
00:39:43,513 --> 00:39:44,839
你有搜查令吗
You have a warrant?

635
00:39:44,876 --> 00:39:46,838
在那之前这更有用
This will serve until a better one comes.

636
00:39:46,876 --> 00:39:48,756
你这岂不是入室抢劫
Why you're a common burglar.

637
00:39:48,793 --> 00:39:50,640
我的朋友是个危险的暴徒
And my friend is a dangerous ruffian.

638
00:39:50,678 --> 00:39:52,401
我们就是要搜你的房子
Together we mean to go through your house.

639
00:39:52,439 --> 00:39:54,815
我没有办法阻止你们
I'm in no position to stop you.

640
00:39:54,816 --> 00:39:56,323
想搜查就搜吧
Search where you will.

641
00:39:56,361 --> 00:39:58,332
我没什么可隐瞒的
I have nothing to hide.

642
00:39:58,725 --> 00:40:02,023
你买的棺材放在哪间屋里了?
Where is the coffin that you had brought into this house?

643
00:40:02,060 --> 00:40:03,784
这和你无关
That is none of your business.

644
00:40:03,822 --> 00:40:05,958
我再说一次 在哪里
I repeat where?

645
00:40:06,900 --> 00:40:07,649
你自说自话冲进我家
Is it not enough

646
00:40:07,687 --> 00:40:10,451
用枪威胁我
that you force your way into my home,

647
00:40:10,489 --> 00:40:12,712
难道还不够吗
that you threaten me at gunpoint,

648
00:40:12,749 --> 00:40:16,609
你还要去打扰死者的安宁吗
must you also now invade the peace of the dead?

649
00:40:16,646 --> 00:40:17,959
在哪里
Where?

650
00:40:18,486 --> 00:40:20,303
我不会告诉你
I shall not tell you.

651
00:40:20,722 --> 00:40:22,233
看住他 华生
Hold him here, Watson.

652
00:40:27,925 --> 00:40:31,803
我不相信你会对 一个手无寸铁的人动手 医生
I don't believe you'd use that on an unarmed man, Doctor,

653
00:40:31,841 --> 00:40:34,272
像我这样的情况
and in my condition.

654
00:40:34,310 --> 00:40:36,371
我在印度的时候是士兵  先生
I was a soldier in India, sir.

655
00:40:36,408 --> 00:40:38,557
我射杀过比你更圣洁的生物
I've shot nobler creatures than you.

656
00:40:38,595 --> 00:40:42,291
灯 华生 灯
Lights, Watson, lights.

657
00:40:45,512 --> 00:40:48,068
我闻到甲醛和收敛剂(凝血作用)了
I smelled formaldehyde and astringent.

658
00:40:58,068 --> 00:40:59,844
感谢上帝
Thank God.

659
00:41:00,504 --> 00:41:02,038
不是她
It's not her.

660
00:41:08,943 --> 00:41:10,120
赶他们出去
Get them out.

661
00:41:10,159 --> 00:41:12,425
你们已经打扰了死者的安息
You have violated the peace of the dead.

662
00:41:12,461 --> 00:41:14,525
你们现在该离开了
You will now leave.

663
00:41:14,564 --> 00:41:16,002
她是谁
Who is she?

664
00:41:16,040 --> 00:41:17,331
赶他们出去
Get them out.

665
00:41:17,368 --> 00:41:19,357
她的名字是Rose Spender
Her name is Rose Spender.

666
00:41:19,395 --> 00:41:20,283
赶他们出去
Get them out.

667
00:41:20,322 --> 00:41:22,002
她是我妻子的老护士
She is my wife's old nurse.

668
00:41:22,040 --> 00:41:25,273
经在这个家已经有半个世纪了
She's been with the family for half a century.

669
00:41:25,310 --> 00:41:26,916
两天前去世了
She died two days ago.

670
00:41:26,954 --> 00:41:29,769
我们明天早上要埋葬她
We are to bury her tomorrow morning.

671
00:41:29,806 --> 00:41:33,080
现在滚出去
Now, get out before I ask the police

672
00:41:33,119 --> 00:41:34,308
趁我还没有叫来警察
you have summoned to my home

673
00:41:34,345 --> 00:41:36,790
统统把你们赶出去
to come in and throw you out.

674
00:42:08,767 --> 00:42:11,444
我在想这个问题 福尔摩斯
I've been considering the problem, Holmes.

675
00:42:13,788 --> 00:42:14,924
在我看来
It does seem to me that they

676
00:42:14,925 --> 00:42:18,420
他们还没有谋杀Frances女士
could not have murdered Lady Frances

677
00:42:18,457 --> 00:42:21,367
并把她的尸体藏进棺材里
and thought to have disposed of her body in that coffin

678
00:42:23,203 --> 00:42:27,765
他们只是要埋葬一个老妇人
for they would then be faced with burying the old lady.

679
00:42:31,871 --> 00:42:34,264
或许这个葬礼和
It may be that this burial has no connection

680
00:42:34,301 --> 00:42:37,122
Frances女士的失踪没有关系
with Lady Frances' disappearance after all.

681
00:42:37,160 --> 00:42:39,679
我说过 正如你所知 她是...
I mean she was, as you know, the most

682
00:42:39,716 --> 00:42:44,610
...最难被人猜测行动的人
unpredictable creature.

683
00:42:44,648 --> 00:42:47,354
也许她对Shlessinger的事又考虑过
It may be that she had second thoughts about Shlessinger.

684
00:42:47,390 --> 00:42:48,946
她也许察觉到了此人
She may even have had some inkling

685
00:42:48,985 --> 00:42:51,651
是我们所想之人
of the kind of man we believe him to be

686
00:42:51,688 --> 00:42:53,795
离开了那里
and removed herself from the house.

687
00:42:53,833 --> 00:42:56,916
毕竟 他很乐意让我们搜查
He was, after all, happy to let us search it.

688
00:43:00,471 --> 00:43:02,175
你怎么想?
What do you think?

689
00:43:07,006 --> 00:43:08,517
你的推理是什么
What is your theory then?

690
00:43:08,556 --> 00:43:10,285
我不知道
I have none.

691
00:43:13,339 --> 00:43:16,472
没有足够的事实来进行推理
There are insufficient facts to construct a theory.

692
00:43:47,817 --> 00:43:50,578
你觉得有东西被你忽略了吗
You think there's something you've overlooked?

693
00:44:26,712 --> 00:44:28,184
延误了
<i>It's late.</i>

694
00:44:29,574 --> 00:44:31,956
早该到了
<i>Well, it should have been there before now.</i>

695
00:44:32,751 --> 00:44:35,574
他们说比起普通的要花更多时间
<i>They say it took longer being out of the ordinary.</i>

696
00:44:48,384 --> 00:44:52,093
上帝赐予我的大脑究竟怎么了
What has happened to any brains that God has given me.

697
00:44:54,501 --> 00:44:56,164
华生
Watson.

698
00:44:57,283 --> 00:44:58,850
快点 伙计
Quick, man.

699
00:44:58,888 --> 00:45:02,652
现在是生死攸关 九死一生
It's life or death. A hundred chances on death and one on life.

700
00:45:11,098 --> 00:45:13,466
哦 万能的上帝 圣主啊
Oh, God most mighty, holy,

701
00:45:13,503 --> 00:45:14,730
最仁慈的救世主
most merciful savior,

702
00:45:14,769 --> 00:45:17,149
我们最可敬的不朽审判者
and our most worthy judge eternal,

703
00:45:17,187 --> 00:45:21,014
请让我们在最后一刻安息...
suffer us not at our last hour for any plains of death...

704
00:45:30,110 --> 00:45:32,846
...勿再延续
and never continuous in one stage.

705
00:45:32,884 --> 00:45:35,550
在生命之中 吾遭遇死亡
In the midst of life, we are in death.

706
00:45:35,589 --> 00:45:39,306
于吾欲拯救 于汝 哦 主啊
Of whom may we seek for succor but of thee, oh, Lord

707
00:45:39,342 --> 00:45:42,275
吾之罪不可恕
who for our sins are justly displeased.

708
00:45:42,313 --> 00:45:45,217
但是 主 上帝 最神圣的...
Yet, oh, Lord God, most holy...

709
00:45:54,662 --> 00:45:57,793
...我们亲爱的姐妹的灵魂已逝
the soul of our dear sister here departed,

710
00:45:57,832 --> 00:46:01,618
我们因此把她的肉体献给土地
we therefore commit her body to the ground.

711
00:46:05,559 --> 00:46:06,879
土归土
Earth to earth,

712
00:46:07,949 --> 00:46:10,158
尘归尘
ashes to ashes,

713
00:46:10,698 --> 00:46:12,849
灰烟尽散
dust to dust

714
00:46:12,886 --> 00:46:14,325
永世...
in sure and certain...

715
00:46:14,327 --> 00:46:15,927
住手
Stop.

716
00:46:17,267 --> 00:46:18,656
把棺材抬上来
Raise that coffin.

717
00:46:20,824 --> 00:46:22,962
你做的一切是要亵渎神灵吗
Whatever do you mean by this sacrilege?

718
00:46:22,999 --> 00:46:24,846
谋生 先生
Murder, sir.

719
00:46:26,547 --> 00:46:28,885
我的意思是谋杀
Murder is what I mean.

720
00:46:28,922 --> 00:46:30,561
对这么娇小的老妇人
Why such a deep coffin

721
00:46:30,598 --> 00:46:32,880
为什么用这么深的棺材
for such a small old lady?

722
00:46:32,918 --> 00:46:34,155
给你们每人一枚金币
A sovereign to each of you

723
00:46:34,193 --> 00:46:36,954
如果能马上打开盖子
if you can lift the lid off that coffin in one minute.

724
00:46:49,995 --> 00:46:51,812
